filters.name: Exchange
filters.description: Stock Exchange at which a stock is listed.

filters.name: Index
filters.description: A major index membership of a stock.

filters.name: Sector
filters.description: The sector which a stock belongs to.

filters.name: Industry
filters.description: The industry which a stock belongs to.

filters.name: Country
filters.description: The country where company of selected stock is based.

filters.name: Market Capitalization
filters.description: Equals The total dollar market value of all of a company's outstanding shares.

filters.name: Price-to-Earnings Ratio
filters.description: A valuation ratio of a company's current share price compared to its per-share earnings (ttm).

filters.name: Forward Price-to-Earnings Ratio
filters.description: A measure of the price-to-earnings ratio using forecasted earnings for the P/E calculation. Value for next fiscal year.

filters.name: Price-to-Earnings-to-Growth
filters.description: A ratio used to determine a stock's value while taking into account earnings growth.

filters.name: Price-to-Sales Ratio
filters.description: P/S number reflects the value placed on sales by the market. It is calculated by dividing the current closing price of the stock by the dollar-sales value per share.

filters.name: Price-to-Book Ratio
filters.description: A ratio used to compare a stock's market value to its book value. It is calculated by dividing the current closing price of the stock by the latest quarter's book value per share.

filters.name: Price-to-Cash Ratio
filters.description: A ratio used to compare a stock's market value to its cash assets. It is calculated by dividing the current closing price of the stock by the latest quarter's cash per share.

filters.name: Price to Free Cash Flow (ttm)
filters.description: A valuation metric that compares a company's market price to its level of annual free cash flow.

filters.name: Earnings Per Share, Growth This Year
filters.description: EPS is the portion of a company's profit allocated to each outstanding share of common stock. EPS serves as an indicator of a company's profitability.Value for current fiscal year.

filters.name: Earnings Per Share, Growth Next Year
filters.description: EPS is the portion of a company's profit allocated to each outstanding share of common stock. EPS serves as an indicator of a company's profitability.Estimate for next fiscal year.

filters.name: Earnings Per Share, Growth Past 5 Years
filters.description: EPS is the portion of a company's profit allocated to each outstanding share of common stock. EPS serves as an indicator of a company's profitability.Annual growth over past 5 years.

filters.name: Earnings Per Share, Growth Next 5 Years
filters.description: EPS is the portion of a company's profit allocated to each outstanding share of common stock. EPS serves as an indicator of a company's profitability.Long term annual growth estimate.

filters.name: Sales Growth Past 5 Years
filters.description: Annual growth over past 5 years.

filters.name: Earnings Per Share, Growth Quarter Over Quarter
filters.description: EPS is the portion of a company's profit allocated to each outstanding share of common stock. EPS serves as an indicator of a company's profitability.Quarter over quarter growth.

filters.name: Sales Growth Quarter Over Quarter (YoY)
filters.description: Quarter over quarter growth compared on a year over year basis.

filters.name: Earnings & Revenue Surprise
filters.description: Company's reported earnings/revenue are above or below analysts' expectations.

filters.name: Dividend Yield (Fiscal Year Estimate)
filters.description: The dividend yield equals the annual dividend per share divided by the stocks price. This measurement tells what percentage return a company pays out to shareholders in the form of dividends.If there is no forward dividend estimate available, trailing twelve month (TTM) value is used.

filters.name: Return on Assets (ttm)
filters.description: An indicator of how profitable a company is relative to its total assets. ROA gives an idea as to how efficient management is at using its assets to generate earnings. Calculated by dividing a company's annual earnings by its total assets, ROA is displayed as a percentage.

filters.name: Return on Equity (ttm)
filters.description: A measure of a corporation's profitability that reveals how much profit a company generates with the money shareholders have invested. Calculated as Net Income / Shareholder's Equity.

filters.name: Return on Investment (ttm)
filters.description: Performance measure used to evaluate the efficiency of an investment or to compare the efficiency of a number of different investments. To calculate ROI, the benefit (return) of an investment is divided by the cost of the investment: (Gain from Investment - Cost of Investment) / Cost of Investment.

filters.name: Current Ratio (mrq)
filters.description: A liquidity ratio that measures a company's ability to pay short-term obligations. Calculated as Current Assets / Current Liabilities.

filters.name: Quick Ratio (mrq)
filters.description: An indicator of a company's short-term liquidity. The quick ratio measures a company's ability to meet its short-term obligations with its most liquid assets. The higher the quick ratio, the better the position of the company. Calculated as (Current Assets - Inventories) / Current Liabilities.

filters.name: Long Term Debt to Equity (mrq)
filters.description: A measure of a company's financial leverage calculated by dividing its long term debt by stockholders' equity. It indicates what proportion of equity and debt the company is using to finance its assets.

filters.name: Total Debt to Equity (mrq)
filters.description: A measure of a company's financial leverage calculated by dividing its liabilities by stockholders' equity. It indicates what proportion of equity and debt the company is using to finance its assets.

filters.name: Gross Margin (ttm)
filters.description: A company's total sales revenue minus its cost of goods sold, divided by the total sales revenue, expressed as a percentage. The gross margin represents the percent of total sales revenue that the company retains after incurring the direct costs associated with producing the goods and services sold by a company. The higher the percentage, the more the company retains on each dollar of sales to service its other costs and obligations.

filters.name: Operating Margin (ttm)
filters.description: Operating margin is a measurement of what proportion of a company's revenue is left over after paying for variable costs of production such as wages, raw materials, etc. A healthy operating margin is required for a company to be able to pay for its fixed costs, such as interest on debt. Calculated as Operating Income / Net Sales.

filters.name: Net Profit Margin (ttm)
filters.description: A ratio of profitability calculated as net income divided by revenues, or net profits divided by sales. It measures how much out of every dollar of sales a company actually keeps in earnings.

filters.name: Payout Ratio
filters.description: The percentage of earnings paid to shareholders in dividends.

filters.name: Insider Ownership
filters.description: Level to which a company is owned by its own management.

filters.name: Insider Transactions
filters.description: A company's shares being purchased or sold by its own management. Value represents 6-month percentual change in total insider ownership.

filters.name: Institutional Ownership
filters.description: Level to which a company is owned by financial institutions.

filters.name: Institutional Transactions
filters.description: A company's shares being purchased or sold by financial institutions. Value represents 3-month change in institutional ownership.

filters.name: Short Selling
filters.description: The amount of short-selling transactions of given stock.

filters.name: Analyst Recommendation
filters.description: An outlook of a stock-market analyst on a stock.

filters.name: Optionable/Shortable
filters.description: Stocks with options and/or available to sell short.

filters.name: Earnings Date
filters.description: Date when company reports earnings.

filters.name: Performance
filters.description: Rate of return for a given stock.

filters.name: Performance 2
filters.description: Rate of return for a given stock.

filters.name: Volatility
filters.description: A statistical measure of the dispersion of returns for a given stock. Represents average daily high/low trading range.

filters.name: Relative Strength Index (14)
filters.description: The Relative Strength Index (RSI) is a technical analysis oscillator showing price strength by comparing upward and downward close-to-close movements.

filters.name: Gap
filters.description: The difference between yesterday's closing price and today's opening price.

filters.name: 20-Day Simple Moving Average
filters.description: 20-Day simple moving average of closing price is the mean of the previous 20 days' closing prices.

filters.name: 50-Day Simple Moving Average
filters.description: 50-Day simple moving average of closing price is the mean of the previous 50 days' closing prices.

filters.name: 200-Day Simple Moving Average
filters.description: 200-Day simple moving average of closing price is the mean of the previous 200 days' closing prices.

filters.name: Change from previous Close
filters.description: The difference between previous's close price and today's last price.

filters.name: Change from Open
filters.description: The difference between today's open price and today's last price.

filters.name: 20-Day High/Low
filters.description: Maximum/minimum of previous 20 days' highs/lows.

filters.name: 50-Day High/Low
filters.description: Maximum/minimum of previous 50 days' highs/lows.

filters.name: 52-Week High/Low
filters.description: Maximum/minimum of previous 52 weeks' highs/lows.

filters.name: All-Time High/Low
filters.description: Maximum/minimum of all-time highs/lows.

filters.name: Pattern
filters.description: A chart pattern is a distinct formation on a stock chart that creates a trading signal, or a sign of future price movements. Chartists use these patterns to identify current trends and trend reversals and to trigger buy and sell signals.

filters.name: Candlestick
filters.description: Candlesticks are usually composed of the body (black or white), an upper and a lower shadow (wick). The wick illustrates the highest and lowest traded prices of a stock during the time interval represented. The body illustrates the opening and closing trades.

filters.name: Beta
filters.description: A measure of a stocks price volatility relative to the market. An asset with a beta of 0 means that its price is not at all correlated with the market. A positive beta means that the asset generally follows the market. A negative beta shows that the asset inversely follows the market, decreases in value if the market goes up.

filters.name: Average True Range
filters.description: A measure of stock volatility. The Average True Range is an exponential moving average (14-days) of the True Ranges. The range of a day's trading is highlow, True Range extends it to yesterday's closing price if it was outside of today's range, True Range =max(high,closeprev)  min(low,closeprev)

filters.name: Average Volume
filters.description: The average number of shares traded in a security per day.

filters.name: Relative Volume
filters.description: Ratio between current volume and 3-month average, intraday adjusted.

filters.name: Current Volume
filters.description: Number of shares traded today.

filters.name: Trades
filters.description: Number of trades today.

filters.name: Price
filters.description: The current stock price.

filters.name: Target Price
filters.description: Analysts' mean target price.

filters.name: IPO Date
filters.description: Date when company had an IPO.

filters.name: Shares Outstanding
filters.description: Shares outstanding represent the total number of shares issued by a corporation and held by its shareholders.

filters.name: Float
filters.description: Float is the number of stock shares that are available for trading to the public. This doesn't include shares held by insiders.

filters.name: After-Hours Close
filters.description: The current stock price in after-hours trading.

filters.name: After-Hours Change
filters.description: The difference between regular trading close price and after-hours price.

filters.name: Latest News
filters.description: Date of the latest reported news.

filters.name: Single Category Designation
filters.description: Single category of each ETF.

filters.name: Commodity Type

filters.name: Social Environmental Type

filters.name: Dividend Type
filters.description: Intended investment objective of holding dividend-oriented stocks as stated in the ETF prospectus.

filters.name: Structure Type

filters.name: Active/Passive

filters.name: Inverse/Leveraged

filters.name: Growth/Value Tilt

filters.name: Market Capilization

filters.name: Developed/Emerging

filters.name: Currency

filters.name: Index Weighting Scheme
filters.description: For ETFs that track an underlying index, this field provides detail on the index weighting type.

filters.name: Sponsor
filters.description: The fund manager (ETF) or issuing bank (ETN).

filters.name: Net Expense Ratio

filters.name: Net Fund Flows
